Title: Gauge Consistent Wilson Renormalization Group II

Authors: Michele Simionato

Comments: 34 pages, 1 eps figure, latex2e. Minor changes, version to appear in

Int. J. Mod. PhysJournal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A15 (2000) 2153-2179

We give a wilsonian formulation of non-abelian gauge theories explicitlyconsistent with axial gauge Ward identitities. The issues of unitarity anddependence on the quantization direction are carefully investigated. Awilsonian computation of the one-loop QCD beta function is performed.